  "description": "MuleRouter provider for Pi \u2014 auto-discovers LLM models via the MuleRouter API",
  "readme": "# pi-mulerouter\n\n[**MuleRouter**](https://mulerouter.ai/) provider for [Pi](https://pi.dev).\n\n## Install\n\n    pi install npm:pi-mulerouter\n\n## Setup\n\n1. Get an API key from [MuleRouter](https://www.mulerouter.ai/app/api-keys)\n2. Set the environment variable:\n\n   export MULEROUTER_API_KEY=\"your-api-key\"\n\n3. Or configure interactively via `/login` in Pi:\n\n   /login\n\nFinally, select _MuleRouter_, and an API key when prompted.\n\n4. Restart Pi (or run `/reload`)\n\n## Models\n\nOnce installed and configured, _MuleRouter_ models are auto-discovered and\nappear in Pi's model selector.\n\n## License\n\n`pi-mulerouter` is licensed under `MIT`. See [LICENSE](LICENSE) for more\ninformation.\n",
